From {{inh|en|enm|argument}},<ref>{{R:MED Online|entry=argūment|pos=n|id=MED2217}}</ref> from {{der|en|xno|-}} and {{der|en|fro|arguement}}, from {{der|en|la|argūmentum|t=argument (for a position); evidence, proof; point, theme; thesis, topic; plot (in theatre)}}, from {{m|la|arguere}} + {{m|la|-mentum|pos={{glossary|suffix}} indicating the instrument, medium, or result of something}}.<ref>{{R:OED Online|pos=n|id=10663|date=March 2021|nodot=1}}; {{R:Lexico|pos=n}}</ref> {{m|la||Arguere}} is the {{glossary|present}} {{glossary|active}} {{glossary|infinitive}} of {{m|la|arguō|t=to argue, assert, declare; to make clear, prove, show; to accuse, charge with, reprove; to blame, censure; to denounce as false}}, either ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*h₂erǵ-|t=silver, white; glittering}}, or from {{der|en|hit||tr=arkuwā(i)-|t=to make a plea, state one’s case}}. The English word is analysable as {{suffix|en|argue|ment|pos2=suffix forming {{glossary|noun}}s from {{glossary|verb}}s, with the sense of ‘the action or result of what is denoted by the verb’}}.

