* {{sense|parameter at a function call}} some authors regard the use of ''argument'' to mean “formal parameter” to be imprecise, preferring that ''argument'' be used to refer only to the value that is used to instantiate the ''parameter'' at runtime, while ''parameter'' refers only to the name in the function definition that will be instantiated.

